"In the commercial world, one of the most valuable assets which a company has is often its name. It is the name which provides an immediate link in the minds of the public with the company's goods or services and the goodwill attached thereto. However, although there is a wealth of statute and case law dealing with the protection of a company's intellectual property rights in its name and trademarks, it is only recently that the English courts have sought to apply it to the Internet, and the vexed area of domain names."
